# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ZHA frontend — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev. In Vercel, add these under
# Project Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase — REQUIRED (the only variables read at runtime).
# From Supabase → Project Settings → API.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# Service-role key — ADMIN/LOCAL ONLY. Used by one-off migration/admin scripts,
# never by the app at runtime. DO NOT add this to Vercel.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ── Audio streaming (hybrid home resolver) ───────────────────────────────────
# YouTube blocks streaming from datacenter IPs (Vercel), even when signed in, so
# audio is resolved by a copy of this app running on a home/residential IP and
# Vercel forwards to it. See DEPLOYMENT.md.
#
# RESOLVER_URL — set ONLY on the hosted (Vercel) deployment: the public tunnel
# URL of the home resolver. The Vercel pipe route forwards audio requests there.
# Leave UNSET on the home resolver itself (otherwise it loops).
# RESOLVER_URL=https://your-tunnel.trycloudflare.com
#
# RESOLVER_TOKEN — optional shared secret. Set the SAME value on Vercel and on the
# home resolver so the public tunnel only serves authorised requests.
# RESOLVER_TOKEN=some-long-random-string
#
# YOUTUBE_COOKIE — optional. A logged-in youtube.com `cookie:` header. Not needed
# on a residential IP; mainly a fallback. Server-only secret. ToS-risky.
# YOUTUBE_COOKIE=VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE=...; __Secure-3PSID=...; ...
